# NotesApp — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- Backend: Java 25 + Spring Boot 4 + PostgreSQL 16
- Frontend: Angular 21 (standalone components, Signals)
- Real-time: STOMP WebSocket
- Auth: JWT (Spring Security)
- Rich text: TipTap (ProseMirror JSON storage)

## Non-negotiable rules

### API
- All REST endpoints MUST be prefixed `/api/v1/` — iOS Phase 2 reuses this API
- Never change an existing endpoint URL without adding a migration path

### Database
- NEVER edit existing Flyway migration files — always create a new `V{n}__description.sql`
- Use PostgreSQL-native tsvector for full-text search (no Elasticsearch)
- Rich text content stored as JSONB (ProseMirror JSON), never raw HTML

### Auth
- Access token: 15 min JWT (Authorization: Bearer header)
- Refresh token: 7 days JWT (HttpOnly cookie only)
- Every endpoint except `/api/v1/auth/**` requires a valid Bearer token

### Testing
- Integration tests MUST use TestContainers with a real PostgreSQL instance — never H2
- Unit tests mock the repository layer only
- Angular tests use Vitest + jsdom

### Frontend
- Use Angular Signals for state — no NgRx, no BehaviorSubject for UI state
- Standalone components only — no NgModules
- Environment config via `src/environments/environment.ts`

### Agents
- Use sub-agents for parallel independent work (frontend / backend / infra)
- Each agent gets a single clear responsibility
